<entry valign="top" align="left" namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Unit 6 Essay Activity:</emphasis><newline/><emphasis effect="bold">How did Franklin Roosevelt respond to the crises of the Great Depression at home and the war against tyrannical states during World War II abroad?</emphasis><newline/><emphasis effect="bold">Option C: Explore the similarities and differences in domestic attitudes about the proper role of the United States in the world during the period c. 1898â€“1945.</emphasis><newline/>Through this inquiry, students will evaluate primary and secondary sources to explain the factors that contributed to a shift in U.S. relations with the rest of the world. Ultimately, students will use the primary and secondary sources in this chapter to practice constructing an essay, in AP Long Essay Question format, demonstrating their skills in explaining historical comparison. Students should be evaluated using the <link url="https://apstudents.collegeboard.org/sites/default/files/2019-05/ap-us-history-course-and-exam-description.pdf">AP Rubric</link>.Assess studentsâ€™ progress in understanding the compelling question for this chapter by assigning <link class="target-chapter" document="m84458">Unit 6 Essay Activity</link>.</entry>
